{{Orphan|date=March 2014}} '''Projexity''' is a Canadian company that offers online audience engagement tools to groups, organizations and municipalities. Projexity's tools have predominantly been used by organizations with strong social impact mandates like the David Suzuki Foundation.
Projexity's tools aim to make it easy for the public to submit content such as events and initiatives to organizations directly through their own websites, effectively transforming any website into a dynamic community hub.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://projexity.com/ |title=About |publisher=Projexity |date= |accessdate=2016-02-17}}</ref> The platform was originally created by designers [[Nicolas Koff]] and [[Marisa Bernstein]], and computer programmer [[Jonathan Koff]] as a means to bring more public engagement and transparency to the often exclusive city building process.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cbc.ca/metromorning/episodes/2013/04/04/crowd-sourcing/ |title=Metro Morning &#124; Crowdsourcing |publisher=CBC.ca |date= |accessdate=2014-03-01}}</ref> Prior to focusing on online engagement tools, Projexity had worked to enable urban improvement projects in both Canada and the United States, ranging from public patios<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.azuremagazine.com/article/six-crowdfunded-projects-were-watching/ |title=Six Crowd-funded Projects We’re Watching – Azure Magazine |publisher=Azuremagazine.com |date=2013-05-31 |accessdate=2014-03-01}}</ref> and information kiosks<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.blogto.com/city/2014/01/ryerson_students_show_astral_how_to_do_street_furniture/ |title=Ryerson students show Astral how to do street furniture |publisher=Blogto.com |date=2014-01-16 |accessdate=2014-03-01}}</ref> to rooftop agriculture.<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.gridphilly.com/grid-magazine/2013/4/9/a-blossoming-vision-for-south-philly-high-school.html |title=Grid - Toward A Sustainable Philadelphia - Home - A blossoming vision for South Philly High School |publisher=Gridphilly.com |date=2013-04-09 |accessdate=2014-03-01}}</ref>
